{"id":"258817343_The_Complexity_of_Proving_That_a_Graph_Is_Ramsey","abstract":"We say that a graph with $n$ vertices is $c$-Ramsey if it does not\ncontain either a clique or an independent set of size $c \\log n$. We\ndefine a CNF formula which expresses this property for a graph $G$. We\nshow a superpolynomial lower bound on the length of resolution proofs\nthat $G$ is $c$-Ramsey, for every graph $G$. Our proof makes use of the\nfact that every Ramsey graph must contain a large subgraph with some of\nthe statistical properties of the random graph.","authors":["Massimo Lauria","Pavel Pudlák","Vojtěch Rödl","Neil Thapen"],"meta":["March 2013Combinatorica 37(2)","DOI:10.1007/978-3-642-39206-1_58","Conference: Proceedings of the 40th international conference on Automata, Languages, and Programming - Volume Part I"],"references":["221580535_Paris-Harrington_Tautologies","3801353_Short_proofs_are_narrow-resolution_made_simple","2370656_Short_Proofs_are_Narrow_-_Resolution_made_Simple","2238359_Pseudorandom_Generators_in_Propositional_Proof_Complexity","345132553_Erdos_on_Graphs_His_Legacy_of_Unsolved_Problems","303568359_Parameterized_Bounded-Depth_Frege_Is_not_Optimal","303568188_Parameterized_bounded-depth_Frege_is_not_optimal","284678693_Some_remarks_on_the_theory_of_graphs","272675777_A_combinatorial_problem_in_geometry","269296610_Parameterized_Proof_Complexity","265547591_Erdos_on_Graphs_His_Legacy_of_Unsolved_Problems","262256044_The_Ramsey_number_R3_t_has_order_of_Magnitude_t2log_t","259764749_Clause-Learning_Algorithms_with_Many_Restarts_and_Bounded-Width_Resolution","244418109_Asympotic_lower_bounds_for_Ramsey_functions","239542839_Canonical_expressions_in_boolean_algebra","232382145_Non-Ramsey_Graphs_Are_clogn-Universal","226603330_A_note_on_propositional_proof_complexity_of_some_Ramsey-type_statements","222801325_A_note_on_Ramsey_numbers","222549341_A_combinatorial_characterization_of_resolution_width","221590755_Examples_of_Hard_Tautologies_in_the_Propositio